(250, 1, '2014-06-16 19:20:21', '2014-06-16 19:20:21', '<i><b>Reducing or limiting access to riparian areas from livestock</b></i>\r\n\r\nLivestock trample riparian areas, this reduces the function of riparian vegetation resulting in increased susceptibility to erosion and flooding, and reduced water quality. Furthermore, the feces and urine from livestock will have a direct impact on water quality.\r\n\r\nThere are different ways that you can limit the number of livestock that enter your watercourses. Depending on what your goals are (simply improving water quality, or improving water quality and terrestrial habitat) the way that these different activities are carried out may vary.', 'Limiting Livestock Access to Waterway''s ', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'limiting-livestock-access-to-waterways', '', '', '2014-06-17 14:18:00', '2014-06-17 14:18:00', '', 184, 'http://localhost/farming/?page_id=250', 0, 'page', '', 0),
